{
  "stem": "150.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We changed apartments.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But other than that, nothing much was affected in my personal life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father got a job.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the one thing that did happen is that Russia and Germany were allies at the time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So naturally, nothing bad could be said about Hitler in the Soviet press or on the Soviet radio.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we really had no idea what the Germans were doing to the Jews in occupied Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We knew that Hitler was an anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the feeling was it's a civilized nation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's an educated nation.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "How bad can it be?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so nobody really worried all that much.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The main worry was, at that particular time towards-- after-- during the first year of Soviet occupation, is that the Soviets were deporting many, many people to the Soviet Union-- all of the intellectuals, all of the businessmen, all of the people who could have been some kind of a resistance.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They deported something like 100,000 Lithuanian citizens, of whom about 25% were Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Totally disproportionate because only about less than 10% of Lithuania's population were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my parents were very much afraid that they, too, would be deported.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And something happened at that time, which I think left an imprint on my life for many, many years to come, namely that a person should basically try to be a good person, even if you don't see much sense in it.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What happened was, I had gone to a summer camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I joined the Communist Youth movement, the Young Pioneers, and they had summer camps.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I went to a summer camp, which was right on the shore of the Baltic.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was  in the border zone, right next to the border with Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't like the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
